s: Early error detection and correction.Measurement: Evaluate process and product effectiveness.Configuration Management: Handle change systematically.Reusability Management: Promote and manage reusable components.Work Product Preparation: Ensure comprehensive documentation.\nproyek berikutnya.Work Product Preparation\n Siapkan dokumentasi lengkap: panduan pengguna, spesikasi sistem, dll.\n47\nInti Konsep:Proses rekayasa perangkat lunakbukanlah aturan kaku.Harusbisa disesuaikanagar cocok dengan:Proyek kecil atau besarTim yang berpengalaman atau masih belajarKebutuhan industri yang berbeda-beda\nContoh Penyesuaian (Adaptation Depends On):\n Project SizeProyek besar (ERP , sistem nasional): butuh proses lengkap, dokumentasi lengkap.Proyek kecil (web toko online sederhana): bisa cukup dengan proses ringan seperti agile.\n Team SkillTim senior: bisa gunakan proses yang lebih eksibel.Tim pemula: butuh panduan lebih ketat agar tidak bingung.\n Domain RequirementsMedis, penerbangan: butuh validasi ketat, proses formal.Startup aplikasi makanan: bisa lebih cepat dan eksibel.\n Stakeholder Involvement48\nProcess AdaptationProcess isn't rigid.It adapts to:Project sizeTeam skillDomain requirementsStakeholder involvementOrganizaAonal culture\n\nJika klien aktif terlibat: cocok dengan pendekatan iteratif seperti Scrum.Jika klien pasif: perlu proses yang lebih terstruktur sejak awal.\n Organizational CulturePerusahaan birokratis: suka proses formal seperti Waterfall.Perusahaan startup: suka metode ringan seperti Lean atau Agile.\n48\nEssence of Software Engineering PracticeInti praktik SE = cara berpikir seperti problem solver\n1. Understand the Problem (Pahami masalahnya dulu)Jangan langsung coding sebelum ngerti masalahnya.Tanyakan: Apa yang dibutuhkan pengguna?Siapa yang terlibat? Apa yang belum diketahui?\nContoh:Sebelum membuat sistem presensi, tanyakan dulu: Apakah mahasiswa bisa login lewat HP? Apakah perlu GPS?\n2. Plan a Solution (Rancang Solusinya)Pecah masalah jadi bagian kecil. Cari pola yang bisa dipakai ulang.Buat alur solusi, pilih teknologi, pecah ke sub-task.\nContoh:Sistem absensi bisa dipecah jadi: login, input lokasi, validasi waktu, simpan ke database.\n3. Carry Out the Plan (Laksanakan rencananya)Mulai coding sesuai desain, jangan loncat-loncat.Ikuti alur desain yang sudah dirancang.Gunakan prinsip traceability: desain  kode  hasil.49\nEssence of Software Engineering PracticeUnderstand the Problem: IdenAfy stakeholders, requirements, unknowns.Plan a SoluAon: Find reusable pa^erns, break down into subproblems.Carry Out the Plan: Follow design roadmap, trace implementaAon.Examine the Result: Apply tesAng and validaAon."Ngana mo bikin aplikasi jang langsung koding, musti ngerti dolo masalahnya, rancang bae, jalankan sesuai rencana, terus periksa ulangkarena software bagus itu lahir dari proses, bukan dari buru-buru!"\nContoh:Kalau kamu sudah buat sketsa UI dan database relasi, ikuti urutannya saat implementasi.\n4. Examine the Result (Periksa hasilnya)Cek: Apakah hasilnya sesuai yang diinginkan?Uji dengan skenario nyata.Validasi output, cek bug, evaluasi kembali desain.\nContoh:Coba login dari HP lain, cek apakah waktu dan lokasi absensi benar tercatat.\n49\nProvide Value  Every feature must add user value\nExample:In a food delivery app, adding aTrack My Orderfeature provides real-time updates and transparency  directly enhancing user experience.\nAnti-example:Adding a ashy animation every time the user switches tabs may look good but adds no real value and slows down performance.2. Keep it Simple (KISS)  Elegant, not overdesigned\nExample:Instead of building a custom calendar widget, a developer integrates Google Calendar API for scheduling. It works well and is easy to maintain.\nAnti-example:A startup builds a full custom time-tracking module with 50+ unused options, making it hard for users and developers alike.3. Maintain the Vision  Protect system integrity\nExample:In a banking app, all teams follow a shared architecture guideline that enforcesconsistent encryption and audit logging.\nAnti-example:50\nHookers Principles of So1ware EngineeringProvide Value Every feature must add user value.Keep it Simple (KISS) Elegant, not overdesigned.Maintain the Vision Protect system integrity.Design for Others Think of maintainers, users.Be Future-Ready Plan for changes.Plan for Reuse Dont reinvent the wheel.Think! Good design begins with good thinking."Bikin bagus, jang ribet, musti pikir panjang, for torang pe masa depan!"(Make it good, dont make it complicated, think aheadfor our future!)\nDevelopers bypass the architecture and hardcode database access, compromising data security and scalability.4. Design for Others  Think of maintainers, users\nExample:A developer writes clear code with comments and meaningful variable names, uses REST API conventions, and provides a README for future teams.\nAnti-example:Functions namedx1()andx2()with 1000+ lines of undocumented code  future developers waste hours trying to understand it.5. Be Future-Ready  Plan for changes\nExample:Instead of hardcoding currency types, the e-commerce app uses a cong le to add/remove currencies dynamically.\nAnti-example:Hardcoded business logic assumes only USD payments  breaks when international expansion happens.6. Plan for Reuse  Dont reinvent the wheel\nExample:An authentication module is designed as a separate reusable service, which can be used across mobile, web, and internal tools.\nAnti-example:Each product team writes their own login ow with dilerent standards and bugs  duplicated elort and inconsistency.\n50\n51\nChapter SummarySoftware  everywhere, critical, evolving.SE structure, discipline, engineering mindset.Process framework: 5 core + umbrella activities.Legacy and AI software need different considerations.Good SE practice prevents failure and promotes growth.\nFacebook algorithm amplifying misinformation: Designed to promote engagement, but ended up fueling echo chambers and spreading false news.Flash crashes in stock markets: Caused by automated trading algorithms acting on rapid data uctuations without human oversight.Facial recognition bias: AI systems misidentifying people of color due to non-diverse training data.Autopilot errors in self-driving cars: Causing accidents in complex real-world scenarios that were not anticipated in training.Google Maps rerouting tra]ic through neighborhoods: Increasing congestion and safety risks in quiet areas.Positively:Increased productivity: Automation in business, nance, education, and healthcare.Global communication: Instant messaging, video calls, and remote collaboration.Access to knowledge: Platforms like Google, Wikipedia, and YouTube empower self-learning.52\nReecHon & Discussion QuesHonsWhat are examples of unintended consequences of software?How has software changed society  positively and negatively?How would you ensure software doesnt deteriorate?Should the same SE process be used for all domains?What risks emerge when software fails in critical systems?\nHealthcare advancement: Software in diagnostics, robotics surgery, and patient monitoring.Negatively:Digital addiction: Social media and games designed for endless engagement.Privacy invasion: Mass data collection and surveillance.Job displacement: Automation replacing repetitive manual jobs.Cybercrime: Hacking, ransomware, and phishing threats are rising.No, the same software engineering process should not be rigidly used for all domains.Why?Di]erent domains have di]erent needs:Medical software: Requires rigorous verication, validation, and compliance (e.g., ISO 13485, FDA).Games: Agile and creative iterations, speed > formality.Banking: Strong security, fault-tolerance, and audit trails.Embedded systems: Must meet hardware constraints and real-time performance.Conclusion: Theframework activities stay the same, but theirimplementation must be tailored(as Pressman notes: SE must be adaptable and agile).\n52	20250603_095733_Introduction_to_Software_Engineerin