gOutputFeedbackThere is sharp dis1nc1on between computer or computer program versus informa1on system\nApa Itu Feedback dalam Sistem Informasi?Feedbackadalah informasi yang dikembalikan ke pengguna atau sistem,untuk mengevaluasi atau memperbaiki input.\nContoh:Mahasiswa input data KRS  sistem kasih feedback: Jadwal bentrok, pilih mata kuliah lain.Admin kampus melihat laporan jumlah mahasiswa aktif  menyusun strategi sosialisasi ulang.\n Jadi, feedback penting agar sistem bisabelajar, mengevaluasi, dan menyesuaikan diri.\nKomputer vs. Sistem InformasiKomponenPenjelasanKomputer / ProgramAlat atau teknologi: laptop, software, serverSistem InformasiKeseluruhan sistem: teknologi + manusia + proses untuk menyelesaikan masalah\n30\nCopyright  2022, 2020, 2018 Pearson Education, Inc. All Rights ReservedWhat is an Informa=on System?                Feedback Output is returned to appropriate members of organiza1on to help evaluate or correct input stageComputer/computer program vs. Informa1on SystemComputers and soJware are technical founda1on and tools, similar to the material used to build a houseInforma(on System is about using these tools to provide solu(on\nFigure 1.4, Page 16.An information system contains information about an organization and its surrounding environment. Three basic activitiesinput, processing, and outputproduce the information organizations need. Feedback is output returned to appropriate people or activities in the organization to evaluate and refine the input. Environmental actors, such as customers, suppliers, competitors, stockholders, and regulatory agencies, interact with the organization and its information systems.The point of this diagram is first of all to highlight the three basic activities of information systems, so that students can understand what an information system is doing at its most fundamental level. But the diagram also puts information systems into the context of organizations (firms), and then puts the firm into its respective