71	6	2	7	\N	essay	[{"question": "Software engineering is described as a layered technology encompassing process, methods, and tools, with quality as its foundation. Elaborate on each of these layers and explain how they contribute to building reliable, adaptable, and maintainable software products. Provide examples of each layer based on the course materials.", "key_points": ["Quality Focus: Foundation for all layers, ensuring high-quality software (minimizing bugs, ease of use, reliability).", "Process Layer: Framework governing how a software project is conducted (communication, planning, modeling, construction, deployment).", "Methods: Technical approaches for tasks like requirements analysis, system design, programming, and testing.", "Tools: Aids to automate or simplify methods and processes (e.g., Visual Studio Code, Git, Trello)."], "suggested_length": "4 paragraphs"}, {"question": "Software Engineering matters for several reasons, including scaling complexity, saving lives and money, supporting evolution, and ensuring quality. Choose two of these reasons and discuss them in detail, providing specific examples from the course materials to illustrate their importance in real-world applications.", "key_points": ["Scales complexity: Helps manage millions of lines of code (e.g., Windows or Android OS).", "Saves lives and money: Software powers critical systems like hospitals, planes, banks (e.g., digital pacemakers, autopilot).", "Supports evolution: Enables continuous improvement and adaptability (e.g., Gojek or Shopee app updates).", "Ensures quality: Via process, testing, and maintenance (e.g., software kasir or aplikasi perbankan before launching)."], "suggested_length": "3 paragraphs"}, {"question": "The Software Process Framework consists of five core activities: Communication, Planning, Modeling, Construction, and Deployment. Describe each activity and explain its significance in the software development lifecycle. Provide a real-world example to illustrate how these activities are applied in a project.", "key_points": ["Communication: Understanding user needs and requirements (e.g., interviewing kantin staff for a kantin app).", "Planning: Defining tasks, timelines, and potential risks (e.g., creating a schedule for app development: design, coding, testing).", "Modeling: Creating system models or designs (e.g., sketching login page, dashboard, and input forms).", "Construction: Coding and testing to find and fix bugs (e.g., creating login feature and testing with fake data).", "Deployment: Releasing software to users and gathering feedback (e.g., uploading kantin app to Play Store beta and receiving user comments)."], "suggested_length": "3 paragraphs"}]	["Rekayasa perangkat lunak terdiri dari:\\r\\nKualitas: Dasar utama agar software andal dan tahan lama. Contoh: cek bug sebelum rilis.\\r\\nProses: Kerangka kerja pengembangan. Contoh: Agile, Waterfall.\\r\\nMetode: Teknik pengembangan. Contoh: UML, desain berorientasi objek.\\r\\nAlat: Software pendukung. Contoh: Git, JUnit.", "1. Kompleksitas\\r\\nSoftware engineering membantu mengelola sistem besar agar tetap terstruktur.\\r\\nContoh: Sistem perbankan butuh desain modular agar tidak mudah gagal.\\r\\n\\r\\n2. Kualitas\\r\\nMenjamin software bebas bug dan sesuai kebutuhan.\\r\\nContoh: Alat medis digital harus lolos uji ketat agar aman digunakan.", "1. Komunikasi: Memahami kebutuhan pengguna.\\r\\n   contoh: Wawancara klien.\\r\\n2. Perencanaan: Atur jadwal dan tugas.\\r\\n   Contoh:Buat timeline proyek.\\r\\n3. Pemodelan: Desain sistem dan UI.\\r\\n   Contoh: gambar diagram alur.\\r\\n4. konstruksi: Coding dan testing.\\r\\n   Contoh: Buat fitur & uji coba.\\r\\n5. Penerapan: Rilis ke pengguna.\\r\\n   Contoh: Upload ke Play Store."]	70	[{"question_index": 0, "score": 70, "feedback": "Answer received. Consider providing more detailed analysis based on course materials.", "user_answer": "Rekayasa perangkat lunak terdiri dari:\\r\\nKualitas: Dasar utama agar softwa